####Use the crystal ball?
/A2/det/useCB 0
#if the 3rd number in the next line is negative use old geometry,
# if positive use new Prakhov geometry
#the first two numbers give the upper and lower air gap between hemispheres
/A2/det/setHemiGap 0.4 0.4 -1 cm
#####Use TAPS?
/A2/det/useTAPS 0
####Configure TAPS
#/A2/det/setTAPSFile taps.dat
#/A2/det/setTAPSZ 175 cm
#/A2/det/setTAPSN 510
/A2/det/setTAPSFile taps07.dat
/A2/det/setTAPSZ 145 cm
/A2/det/setTAPSN 384
/A2/det/setTAPSPbWO4Rings 2
####Use the PID
#### 1 = PID I, 2 = PID II, 3 = PID III (30cm @ rin = 3.3cm)
#### Option 3 requires PIDZ offset of 2.5cm to fit in new lightguides
/A2/det/usePID 3
/A2/det/setPIDZ 2.5 cm
#### Use a nested PID? This option constructs PID II outside PID III
#### Warning requires PID III and no wire chamber!
#### Needs Z offset of ~20cm so as not to overlap with lightguides of PID III
/A2/det/useNestPID 1
/A2/det/setNestPIDZ 22.0 cm
####Use the Polarimeter
####1 = Use Phase I (2009), 2 = Use Phase II (2015/2016, 2.6cm), 3 = Use Phase II (2015/2016, backup tube 2.25cm)
#### 30cm long polarimeter requires offset of 3.8 cm (PID option 3)
/A2/det/usePol 0
#### For the P2 polarimeter only, P1 ALWAYS has a cap. Set to 0 for no cap or 1 for cap (requires shorter PID, options 3/4)
/A2/det/usePolCap 0
/A2/det/setPolZ 3.8 cm

#set to 1 to not create the anode wires, 2 to create the anode wires
#Phase 2 polarimeter proposal had MWPCZ offset of -5cm (why?)
/A2/det/useMWPC 0
/A2/det/setMWPCZ 0.0 cm

####Use Cherenkov?
/A2/det/useCherenkov 0

/A2/det/useTOF 0
/A2/det/setTOFFile TOF.par
##Set the target
/A2/det/useTarget Cryo
## If using Cryo select target version
## 1 for old 4.1cm radius target, 2 for new 3.1cm radius target
/A2/det/useCryoTgt 2
###Cryo targets : G4_lH2, A2_lD2###
/A2/det/targetMaterial A2_lD2
/A2/det/setTargetLength 10. cm
